      "title": "Better Late Than Never \u23f0",
      "content": "Sometimes you don't know the variable's value immediately, but you promise it won't be null when used.\n\nUse the `late` keyword."
    },
    {
      "id": "s_ch8_l2_2",
      "type": "code",
      "title": "Using Late",
      "content": "Initializing later:",
      "codeSnippet": "late String dinner;\n\nvoid main() {\n  dinner = 'Pizza'; \n  print(dinner);\n}",
